# Socket

The cool thing about sockets is that they are focused on transferring the *data*, so you can write the client and server code in different languages and it doesn't matter.

[python socket](https://docs.python.org/3/library/socket.html)

[python socket example](https://docs.python.org/release/2.5.2/lib/socket-example.html)

[sockets c++ the geekstuff](https://www.thegeekstuff.com/2011/12/c-socket-programming/)

[node JS websocket](https://www.w3schools.com/nodejs/nodejs_raspberrypi_webserver_websocket.asp)


